Socio-PLT: Programming Language Perceptions

What is Socio-PLT? | Video | Further Resources | Created by Leo Meyerovich and Ari Rabkin (EECS @ Berkeley)

Visualizations: Language/statement ranking Statement correlation Language correlation Statement clustering Language clustering

Explore how programmers rank languages by different criteria

  • Look at circles: see how well a statement matches a language by examining circles. Bigger and greener means stronger agreement. Transparent means low data or high contention. Mouse over to show the score (0-100) and 95% confidence interval.
  • Click on circles: sort the languages according to the statement. Click again to reverse. High deviation languages are suppressed by using the formula "rank = score - 3 * deviation."
  • Zoom with browser controls: on a mac, use command-+, command--, and command-0
  • Click on the language axis: sort by language. Click again to reverse.
  • Toggle all statements and all languages:. Refine further with checkboxes.
  • Fisheye mouse zoom: points x axis y axis
